iof our campus due to excessive construction during my two years		gopher.black	70
iattending. There was no grass over the vast majority of the		gopher.black	70
icampus, only churned earth or piled dirt next to broken cement		gopher.black	70
iwalkways. I don't remember much of the article except that I used		gopher.black	70
ithe word "agrestic" in a way that suggested rural beauty. The		gopher.black	70
ieditor of the paper had enormous issue with the word, claiming it		gopher.black	70
iwasn't a real word at all (her three degrees in English literature		gopher.black	70
ias proof). This outrage and logical fallacy cemented "agrestic" in		gopher.black	70
imy mind forever. Funny how brains work [0].		gopher.black	70
